Fundamental concepts of the multimedia production. A look into text, graphics, sound, video making and editing and according software. Introducing techniques for rich text, graphics, sound and video editing and software tools to support these activities.
Lectures and practical exercises are supported by the web-based learning environment Moodle (discussions, assignments, grading).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will acquire the fundamental concepts, techniques and basic skills for multimedia production.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student will be able to: 1. define multimedia basic terms; 2. choose basic components of multimedia hardware and outline features of various models; 3. use raster graphics for editing pictures; 4. use 2D and 3D graphics for creating and editing images; 5. create, save and process videos and audio clips; 6. create simple animations.
